.TH "drm_gem_cma_get_unmapped_area" 9 "drm_gem_cma_get_unmapped_area" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_cma_get_unmapped_area \- propose address for mapping in noMMU cases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" drm_gem_cma_get_unmapped_area
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long len "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pgoff "  ","
.BI "unsigned long flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
file object
.IP "addr" 12
memory address
.IP "len" 12
buffer size
.IP "pgoff" 12
page offset
.IP "flags" 12
memory flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used in noMMU platforms to propose address mapping
for a given buffer.
It's intended to be used as a direct handler for the struct
\fIfile_operations.get_unmapped_area\fP operation.
.SH "RETURN"
mapping address on success or a negative error code on failure.
